rComments: Professor Woodcock is a mediocre professor. His lectures, though, are extremely dull. He says you need the textbook to pass but his lecture slides are enough. His midterm and exams are pretty easy if you attend and listen in class and study for them. His case studies are easy marks and a great way to raise your mark.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Not a very good prof. his lectures are very boring. Test and Quiz are all related to the textbook.........

This guy is quite possibly one of the rudest profs I've ever had. He was racist and made derogatory comments towards my culture as well as negative comments towards people with disabilities. He is extremely dry in lectures and you will probably fall asleep. If you can avoid having him, do it.

He is a really nice guy but the course itself is an intro course so it's not terribly interesting to begin with. He reads the powerpoint so just read it yourself and stay home. The midterm was a breeze, I had another midterm that day so I studied 30 minutes for it and got a mark in the high 80's. If you took business in high school you'll be fine.

I'm not exaggerating when I say he just reads his slides. Emailed him two months ago and have yet to receive a response. Doesn't put up course material in time, including assignments and slides for class that evening. Not helpful and just overall poor quality of teaching.

nice guy, easy material but unorganized, never answers emails, or phone calls. I walked into the final with a 90, but received a failing grade and when I called (it took him 3 weeks to get back to me) he said he didn't have either of my midterms (even though I had the grades up on blackboard). he fixed my grade but unacceptable in my opinion

He's a nice guy, but because the class is so light, you hardly need to pay attention, and it just becomes a drag if you go to the 3 hour lectures. But he's an easy grader, and the material is easy enough.  I can say that throughout the entire semester, I worked maybe 35 hours total for this class and I'm still doing very well.

Prof. Woodcock is a really nice guy. He has clearly done a lot of consulting for companies in Canada and the US and has some good experience and understanding of the business world. His exams and group projects are very straight forward and he truly wants students to succeed. Easy marker. Funny guy and his wife jokes are hilarious!
really great guy! easy material!
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: In my person opinion, this class is boring and dull but you'll get a good grade. You don't even have to go to class.
Unprepared for class. Just reads ppt slides. No  point attending class. As a student i expect more for my money. Its time for this guy to go!

He would go through the slides in a monotone way and explains every thing on them throughly that it ends up being boring. He's slow at marking the memos and exams. Really, don't even bother show up to class.. Just form a group, get the memos done and read the textbook and the testbank.

Nice guy, but pretty boring material. Two group projects that are graded very easy. I found the midterm and exam easy, but if you don't review the notes and read the textbook a little you will crash and burn. Put in moderate effort and you'll get a good mark.

He definitely has no idea what he is talking about in class. Just read the PPT and say something unnecessary. There is no need to go to class unless you want to get information about the memo. He lets you choose your group, and will give you high mark on group memo as long as you do it carefully and follow the instruction.
Super easy class
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Group projects']

rComments: Straight forward professor, students should not have issues understanding the content. Very easy class as well, you can pass without studying too much. The material can be dry as it is not crazy engaging, but I found that I could skip and still catch up.
He's a good professor. The classes are not that interesting tbh. Just do the work and you'll pass

A very straightforward class, since it's just the basics of business. If you show up, take good notes, and contribute well to the memos, it's impossible not to do well. I barely opened the textbook since his slides are pretty much identical to what's in the textbook. The tests are fairly clear-cut and he even posts examples on Blackboard.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Group projects']

rComments: He did some work before becoming a teacher. He gives good examples when comparing to the real world.
Everything you need is on the slides, however it's fun hearing him talk. In fact the only reason why I go to lectures is to listen to him say whatever.
Pretty boring professor.  I did 0 studying in this course and still pulled off a decent mark.
very unorganized and boring

This class was pretty dull if you don't do the readings. Trust me you will have to read the textbook to do decent, and go to lectures to do amazing. He is very vague on his group assignments so good luck, for us we worked hard on our opinions, and we got great marks.

Great prof, open to discussion always. The class is fairly boring as it is a cut and dry intro to business course. Honestly, I didn't expect much more from him excitement-wise. His expectations for midterms / finals are very clear, with mostly MC questions. The group projects (written memos) are easy to coordinate and not difficult either.

Honestly, lectures are boring AF.. I went to 2-3 lectures the entire semester and my final mark was a 85, the memos were SUPER easy (less than one page per person, only two memos per year) and I got between 84-93 on my memos.   Take this if you want an easy elective with straight-forward content and if you don't want to go to class at all :)
Most boring professor ever in my entire university career.... He is incredibly monotone; it's impressive how he pulls that off so easily... unfortunately. group tasks are terrible.

Nice person who is kind to his students but does not make the course very interesting. He is a good guy with good intentions but makes little effort to enhance the course material. Group project was awful and there are many students in the class who do not take the work seriously. Make sure you have friends to work with.

A good person, who wants his students to succeed. His tests and exams are super easy, mostly multiple choice and you just need to read the text to get a good grade. Marks fairly in the memos. Take his class if you're looking for an easy A.

He's a good prof and lectures weren't too bad (dull though, it's intro to business). I went to class and listened (a lot of the course is common sense and good judgment), and got a decent mark without a textbook. Show up, listen, and know your terminology and definitions. You'll do fine. I'm in engineering and did so, that should tell you enough.
Lectures are a little dry, but with Grade 10 criteria they'd better be.
Very chill guy. I'd recommend him for this course for sure!

The class is extremely boring. The lectures and material are so dry. Assignment group work is annoying as well. The exams weren't too hard and you really just needed to read the textbook and review his slides to do well. Grading was odd cause all members of our assignment groups received the same grade. He was quite a nice person though.

Awesome prof! Content of the course was dry but the lectures were helpful and very clear. The exams were pretty easy and reflected the course well. He even gave out practice exams and told us what to review. The memos were practical and you can choose which ones to do that works with your schedule. Very helpful and just an overall really nice guy.

Great prof. overall, love the fact he gave as a project every week and let us choose which projects fit our schedule best. Loved class as he made it as interesting as he could. Recommend this prof too all
Makes an attempt to engage the class in discussion, which is nice, but the course overall was very boring.

Great class. The prof was very clear and could explain the topics effectively and provide interesting examples. If you paid attentions, he was quite funny. Really enjoys what he's doing and wants to help students do well.

He was awesome and one of my best profs, he engages the class and if you're paying attention you're sure to have fun. His exams were as he said and he did a good job on the delivery of the subject. Best prof for this course
Terrible prof, poor lecturer, disorganized, boring, grading is seemingly random, does not stick to syllabus. Avoid at all cost!
Not very interesting prof. Gives good outlines of what's going to be tested, but has a hard time answering questions and explaining things himself
Prof was incredibly knowledgable, other profs could take notes on his ballin teaching style. still believes in the goodness and innocence of students. Could rave on but character limits prevent

Had him for strategic management and project management. His slides are very inconsistent with the textbook in project management. Also, he seems to procrastinate with designing exams, and preparing his lecture before the class. He seldomly can come up with examples quickly when a student asks for one and overall just seems unprepared.

Should be spending time teaching the intopia simulation to give his students a fighting chance at a decent mark - lied about how the course would be evaluated - syllabus has a 10% peer evaluation but he changed that to his own evaluation without telling us - didn't give out a single A or A+.. 83.4 was highest mark in class - This guy is heartless.
why go through dry and boring lectures when the material isn't testable?
Extremely boring lectures and memo guidelines were too strict. Did not learn anything in this class.
He is extremely knowledgeable and makes you look at problems from mutliple angles.
everyone just sits around in his classes and makes fun of his name :( my only suggestion to him, as a teacher is to change his last name to stewart or johann.
Prof. woodcock is very nice to every student. and he helps us out in our cases.
